data.quick-start#Quick Start:
For a normal JavaScript project, you'll first need to import Million's basic functions:
import { m, createElement, patch } from 'million';

If you want to use a templating language like JSX,
read more here about using JSX
with Million
Then, you can start building your app (e.g. Counter app):
import { m, createElement, patch } from 'million';

const view = (seconds) => m('p', undefined, [`Time elapsed: ${seconds}`]);

const el = createElement(view(0));

let seconds = 0;

setInterval(() => {
  patch(el, view(seconds));
  seconds++;
}, 1000);

document.body.appendChild(el);
